text: Erika Fisch (29 April 1934 – 9 November 2021) was a German athlete. She represented the United Team of Germany at the 1956 Summer Olympics in Melbourne. She came in fourt place in the long jump. During the 1962 European Athletics Championships she won silver in the 4 × 100 m relay. Fisch died on 9 November 2021, at the age of 87.Erika Fisch Verstorben ==References== Category:1934 births Category:2021 deaths Category:Olympians for Germany Category:German athletes
